track_notes: Visited on a non firing day with XYL. The MoD have now metalled a narrow strip of road up to SX 590913 where there is room to park and turn round. Easy 43 minute walk up on tracks to near Yes Tor and then a well trodden path across the moor to summit. Useful small pointy rock a few feet down from summit to fix your pole to.
track_title: High Willhays from last parking place

track_notes:
Route taken from Okehampton Camp. In vehicle, after passing check point, turn left immediately and follow road as far as allowed. There is space for a number of vehicles to park. Road had good surface to all way to parking spot at SX 5908 9128.
Follow 4x4 track until SX 5809 8992 where a fairly well defined track breaks off to left towards High Willhays. At this point, Yes Tor, the more obvious summit will be above to right.

Total time (including ops): 2hr 40m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: High Willhays Linear from Halstock Road. Jun 2020.
